The crawler is setup to be very polite. So compared to something like  
httrack it will seem slow.

You need to make sure your scope is setup properly so that the  
crawler doesn&#39;t just wander off over the internet. For a single site  
the domain scope is great. As you get more experience you can  
experiment with the others. Read the help text carefully.

The next port of call for a beginner are the logs - they will let you  
see what is going on during the crawl. If it wanders off or does  
something unexpected you can pause it and tweak the settings mid run.  
By watching these and experimenting you will get a good feel for what  
the various settings do. Crawling your own site is always a good  
starting point because you know what its there and exactly what to  
expect.

Lastly (but certainly not least) - upgrade to a more recent version  
of Heritirx if you can - 1.4 has lots of little features that make  
using it a more pleasant experience. Well worth the effort.

cheers

mark





